condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Bank's Safeguard Policies | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall ensure that that the terms ofreference for any consultancy in respect to Part 3 of the Project shall be satisfactory to the World Bank following its reviewthereof and, to that end, such terms of reference shall duly incorporate the requirements of the Bank Safeguards Policies then inforce, as applied to the advice conveyed through such technical assistance. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
Finance Agreement :EMF and RPF | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall carry out the Project in accordance with theEMF and RPF. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :EMP | Description :Upon identification of the zone of impact of any Project activity under Part 1 of theProject, and prior to carrying out of any activities, the Project Implementing Entity shall: (a) carry out an environmentalassessment of each said activity and thereafter prepare EMPs in accordance with the EMF, and (b) implement the EMP in accordancewith its terms. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Independent Verification Reports | Description :For purposes of Part 1(h)(4)(B) of the Project, the ProjectImplementing Entity shall cause the Independent Verification Agent to: (a) carry out once each calendar quarter a technicalverification of compliance of the work performed by NSWMA, the CBOs and Environmental Wardens; and (b) prepare an IndependentVerification Report of as set forth in the Project Operational Manual. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :PIU | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall operate and maintain, throughout the implementation ofthe Project, a Project Implementation Unit (“PIU”), with functions, staffing, and responsibilities satisfactory to the Bank as setforth in the Project Operational Manual. | Completed: February 2014

Finance Agreement :Project Operational Manual | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall carry out the Project inaccordance with the provisions of the Project Operational Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :RAP | Description :Prior to the carrying out of any activity under Part 1 of the Project that involvesResettlement, the Project Implementing Entity shall prepare the corresponding Resettlement Action Plan (RAP) in accordance with theRPF, in form and substance satisfactory to the Bank, and immediately thereafter carry out the relevant RAP in accordance with itsterms. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Subsidiary Agreement | Description :To facilitate the carrying out of the Project, the Borrower shall make theproceeds of the Loan available to the Project Implementing Entity under a subsidiary agreement (the Subsidiary Agreement) betweenthe Borrower and the Project Implementing Entity, under terms and conditions satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :14-Sep-2015

Finance Agreement: NSWMA RB Agreement | Description: To facilitate the carrying out of Part 1(h)(4)(A) of the Project, the ProjectImplementing Entity shall enter into a results-based agreement with NSWMA (the NSWMA RB Agreement), under terms and conditionssatisfactory to the Bank and elaborated in the Project Operational Manual. | Due Date:30-May-2016

Finance Agreement: RB Agreement | Description: To further facilitate the carrying out of Part 1(h)(4)(B) of the Project, theProject Implementing Entity shall enter into a separate results-based agreement with each Community-Based Organization andEnvironmental Warden (a RB Agreement), under terms and conditions satisfactory to the Bank and elaborated in the ProjectOperational Manual. | Due Date: 30-Jun-2016

Finance Agreement: Retaining an Independent Verification Agent | Description :For purposes of Part 1(h)(4)(B) of the Project, theProject Implementing Entity shall retain an Independent Verification Agent with qualifications and experience, and under terms ofreference acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date:30-Jun-2016
